{
  "texts": [
    "Future systems may conduct surveys, monitor app-based interactions, and flag potential emergencies for clinician review.",
    "There is also an opportunity to train AI agents based on SLM using discipline-specific data, particularly for counseling individuals with neurological, genetic, or fluency-related disorders, provided these tools are rigorously developed and evaluated.",
    "Such applications could support the care team but only if accompanied by robust safety filters and ethical safeguards (Amodei et al., 2016; Bengio, 2024).",
    "While AI can supplement counseling efforts, it cannot replace the therapeutic relationship between a clinician and a client.",
    "SLPs play a role in prevention by promoting the early identification of communication disorders and addressing associated risk factors."
  ]
}